      "id": "proving-languages-not-regular-svg",
      "title": "Proving Languages Not Regular",
      "description": "Visual diagram for Proving Languages Not Regular",
      "type": "animated-svg",
      "file": "../../../assets/TOC_proving-languages-not-regular.svg",
      "animated": false,
      "svgContent": "<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"420\" height=\"350\" viewBox=\"0 0 420 350\"><defs><linearGradient id=\"bg\" x1=\"0%\" y1=\"0%\" x2=\"0%\" y2=\"100%\"><stop offset=\"0%\" style=\"stop-color:#E3F2FD\"/><stop offset=\"100%\" style=\"stop-color:#BBDEFB\"/></linearGradient><marker id=\"arrowhead\" markerWidth=\"10\" markerHeight=\"7\" refX=\"9\" refY=\"3.5\" orient=\"auto\"><polygon points=\"0 0, 10 3.5, 0 7\" fill=\"#1565C0\"/></marker></defs><rect width=\"420\" height=\"350\" fill=\"url(#bg)\" rx=\"12\"></rect><text x=\"210\" y=\"25\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-family=\"Arial\" font-size=\"13\" font-weight=\"bold\" fill=\"#1565C0\">\n    Proving Languages Not to be Regular\n    \n  </text><!-- Pumping Lemma Box --><rect x=\"30\" y=\"50\" width=\"360\" height=\"60\" fill=\"#2196F3\" rx=\"5\"></rect><text x=\"210\" y=\"75\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-family=\"Arial\" font-size=\"11\" fill=\"white\">\n    Pumping Lemma: For any regular language L, ∃ p (pumping length) such that\n    \n  </text><text x=\"210\" y=\"90\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-family=\"Arial\" font-size=\"11\" fill=\"white\">\n    if s ∈ L and |s| ≥ p, then s = xyz with conditions (1) |xy| ≤ p, (2) |y| ≥ 1, (3) xyⁱz ∈ L ∀ i ≥ 0\n    \n  </text><!-- Proof Strategy Box --><rect x=\"30\" y=\"120\" width=\"360\" height=\"50\" fill=\"#64B5F6\" rx=\"5\"></rect><text x=\"210\" y=\"140\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-family=\"Arial\" font-size=\"11\" fill=\"white\">\n    Proof Strategy: Assume L is regular → apply pumping lemma → find contradiction\n    \n  </text><text x=\"210\" y=\"155\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-family=\"Arial\" font-size=\"11\" fill=\"white\">\n    ∴ L is not regular\n    \n  </text><!-- Example Languages --><rect x=\"30\" y=\"180\" width=\"360\" height=\"110\" fill=\"#1565C0\" rx=\"5\"></rect><text x=\"210\" y=\"195\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-family=\"Arial\" font-size=\"11\" font-weight=\"bold\" fill=\"white\">\n    Example Non-Regular Languages:\n    \n  </text><text x=\"210\" y=\"215\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-family=\"Arial\" font-size=\"11\" fill=\"white\">\n    {aⁿbⁿ | n ≥ 0} (equal number of a's and b's)\n    \n  </text><text x=\"210\" y=\"235\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-family=\"Arial\" font-size=\"11\" fill=\"white\">\n    {ww | w ∈ {a,b}*} (strings repeated twice)\n    \n  </text><text x=\"210\" y=\"255\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-family=\"Arial\" font-size=\"11\" fill=\"white\">\n    {aⁿ² | n ≥ 0} (strings with quadratic length)\n    \n  </text><text x=\"210\" y=\"275\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-family=\"Arial\" font-size=\"11\" fill=\"white\">\n    {aᵐbⁿ | m > n} (more a's than b's)\n    \n  </text><!-- Arrow showing proof flow --><path d=\"M210,55 L210,115\" stroke=\"#1565C0\" stroke-width=\"2\" marker-end=\"url(#arrowhead)\"></path><path d=\"M210,125 L210,175\" stroke=\"#1565C0\" stroke-width=\"2\" marker-end=\"url(#arrowhead)\"></path><!-- Key Insight --><rect x=\"30\" y=\"300\" width=\"360\" height=\"35\" fill=\"#2196F3\" rx=\"5\"></rect><text x=\"210\" y=\"320\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-family=\"Arial\" font-size=\"11\" fill=\"white\">\n    Key Insight: Finite automata cannot count or remember unbounded information\n    \n  </text></svg>",
